When you're in the mood for the flavors of a classic turkey sandwich, but feel
like switching up your game a little, this wrap is just what you need. It's got
all those deli feels we love at lunchtime: thinly sliced turkey breast, crunchy
cukes, sliced tomato, and crisp lettuce dressed in a sweet, zingy honey Dijon
dressing all rolled into a soft flour tortilla (with lots of salad left over for
a side). We just love a wrap—it's more portable and less soggy come lunchtime,
and we're all about planning ahead.

Wash and dry produce.

Trim and discard root end from @Baby Lettuce{1} unit; roughly chop. Halve
@Tomato{1} unit lengthwise; thinly slice into half-moons. Thinly slice
@Mini Cucumber{1} unit into rounds.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @Honey Dijon Dressing{1.5%ounce} and
@Mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}.

Place lettuce, tomato, and cucumber in a #large bowl{}; drizzle with as much
creamy dressing as you like. Toss to combine and season with @Salt{} and
@Pepper{}.

Wrap @Flour Tortillas{2} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until warm and
pliable, ~{30%seconds}.

Place tortillas on a clean work surface. Place half the salad on the bottom
two-thirds of each tortilla; top with half the @Sliced Turkey Breast{8%ounce}
(all for 4 servings). Fold up bottom side of each tortilla over filling, then
roll tortillas up tightly, starting with filled sides, to form wraps.

Halve wraps on a diagonal and divide between plates. Serve with remaining salad
on the side.